Carrizo Oil & Gas Target of Unusually Large Options Trading (NASDAQ:CRZO)
Xavier Trudeau
Juillet 24, 2017



Part












Cim Investment Mangement Inc. now owns 15,402 shares of the oil and gas producer's stock worth $575,000 after buying an additional 9,173 shares during the last quarter. (NASDAQ:CRZO) will release their quarterly results. Ten analysts have issued estimates for Carrizo Oil & Gas' earnings. Three research analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, five have assigned a hold rating, thirteen have issued a buy rating and one has assigned a strong buy rating to the stock.
On average, analysts expect that Carrizo Oil & Gas will report full year earnings of $1.11 per share for the current fiscal year, with EPS estimates ranging from $0.72 to $1.49.From another technical standpoint, Carrizo Oil & Gas, Inc. The business had revenue of $151.36 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $147.19 million. During the same period in the prior year, the business posted $0.16 earnings per share. The firm's revenue was up 86.3% on a year-over-year basis.Several research firms have weighed in on CRZO. Royal Bank Of Canada reaffirmed a "buy" rating and set a $47.00 price objective on shares of Carrizo Oil & Gas in a report on Friday, March 31st.Wall Street sell-side research analysts covering Whitewave Foods Company (The) (NYSE:WWAV) shares have recently provided various price target projections on where the stock might be going. Robert W. Baird dropped their price objective on shares of Carrizo Oil & Gas from $50.00 to $36.00 and set an "outperform" rating on the stock in a report on Wednesday, May 24th. Credit Suisse Group restated a neutral rating and set a $38.00 target price on shares of Carrizo Oil & Gas in a research report on Friday, June 2nd.On December 6 analysts at Raymond James began coverage of the stock with an initial rating of "Strong Buy". The company now has an average rating of Buy and an average price target of $40.72.In other news, Director Frank A. Wojtek sold 2,800 shares of the firm's stock in a transaction on Tuesday, May 16th. Tortoise Capital Advisors Llc sold 8,835 shares as the company's stock declined 26.59% while stock markets rallied. Following the completion of the transaction, the director now owns 30,008 shares in the company, valued at $727,393.92. The sale was disclosed in a legal filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which can be accessed through this hyperlink.A number of large investors have recently added to or reduced their stakes in the stock. State of Alaska Department of Revenue now owns 6,760 shares of the oil and gas producer's stock valued at $193,000 after buying an additional 120 shares during the last quarter. Teachers Retirement System of The State of Kentucky now owns 17,000 shares of the oil and gas producer's stock worth $635,000 after buying an additional 1,900 shares during the last quarter. Russell Investments Group Ltd. acquired a new position in Carrizo Oil & Gas during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $4,627,000.Lazard Asset Management LLC lowered its position in shares of Carrizo Oil & Gas, Inc. Macquarie Group Ltd. now owns 723,479 shares of the oil and gas producer's stock worth $27,022,000 after buying an additional 42,356 shares during the last quarter. Elkfork Partners LLC bought a new stake in shares of Carrizo Oil & Gas during the fourth quarter valued at $132,000. Bnp Paribas Arbitrage owns 0.29% invested in Visa Inc (NYSE:V) for 780,859 shares. "(CRZO) to Neutral" was originally posted by Sports Perspectives and is the sole property of of Sports Perspectives. If you are accessing this story on another publication, it was illegally copied and republished in violation of USA & global trademark and copyright legislation. The original version of this report can be read at https://transcriptdaily.com/2017/07/22/lazard-asset-management-llc-has-204000-stake-in-carrizo-oil-gas-inc-crzo-updated-updated-updated.html. (NASDAQ:HAIN) shares were last seen up 2.52% at $42.79, which is -2.78% lower than the previous trading session. The stock is above its 52-week low with 37.99% and is in the wake of its 52-week high with -24.92%.A stock rating usually tells investors how well a stock's market value relates to what analysts think is a fair value for the stock, based on an independent evaluation of the company.Legacy Oil + Gas had its " rating reiterated by analysts at TD Securities. The Company is engaged in the exploration, development and production of oil and gas from resource plays located in the United States.

 




