Hot Stocks
Carrizo Oil & Gas, Inc. (CRZO) has a value of $16.40 per share While Mueller Water Products, Inc. (MWA) is stand at $11.69By Braden Nelson - June 30, 2017031
Share on Facebook
Tweet on Twitter


Carrizo Oil & Gas, Inc. (CRZO) Stock Price Movement:In recent trading day Carrizo Oil & Gas, Inc. (CRZO) stock showed the move of 5.06% with the closing price of $16.40. Closing price generally refers to the last price at which a stock trades during a regular trading session. The company moved in the past week with shift of 2.31%. Over the last three months, the shares of the company have changed -40.62% and performed -56.77% over the last six months.    Return on equity reveals how much profit a company earned in comparison to the total amount of shareholder equity found on the balance sheet. It has a return on equity (ROE) of 582.90%. Tracking ROA value which gives an idea as to how efficient management is at using its assets to generate earnings. The firm has a Return on Assets (ROA) value of -20.80%. However it has a net margin of -63.10%. Its Average True Range (ATR) shows a figure of 1.12. The stock currently has Monthly Volatility of 6.21% and Weekly Volatility of 6.07%. The Beta for the stock stands at 2.02. The consensus recommendation for stock is 1.90. The rating scale runs from 1 to 5 with 5 indicating a Strong Sell, 1 indicating a Strong Buy and 3 indicating a Hold. Technical Indicators Summary: Investors and Traders continue to monitor technical levels of shares of Carrizo Oil & Gas, Inc. (CRZO). A frequently used tool among technical stock analysts is the moving average. Moving averages are considered to be lagging indicators that simply take the average price of a stock over a certain period of time. Moving averages can be very helpful for identifying peaks and troughs. They may also be used to assist the trader figure out proper support and resistance levels for the stock. The stock closing price is currently trading downward to its 50 day moving average with change of -26.64%, tumbled to its 20 day moving average with figure of -13.44% and behind its 200 day moving average with value -48.69%. The share last price represents downtick move of -62.69% in value from company’s 52-Week high price and shows 6.49% above change in value from its 52-Week low price. Checking in on some other technical levels, the 14-day RSI is currently at 32.61. June 30, 2017 Carrizo Oil & Gas, Inc. (CRZO) announced that it has priced an underwritten public offering of $250.0 million aggregate principal amount of senior notes due 2025 under its existing shelf registration statement. The offering is expected to close on July 14, 2017, subject to customary closing conditions. Carrizo intends to use the net proceeds from this offering to fund a portion of the purchase price for the pending acquisition of approximately 16,488 net acres located in the Delaware Basin (the “Pending Acquisition”) and for general corporate purposes. Pending the closing of the Pending Acquisition, Carrizo intends to use the net proceeds from this offering to reduce borrowings under its revolving credit facility. Carrizo intends to use net proceeds from this offering not used to pay the purchase price for the Pending Acquisition for general corporate purposes, including to fund future potential acquisitions or a portion of its 2017 and 2018 capital expenditure plans.Mueller Water Products, Inc. (MWA) stock moved with shift of 3.54% in the past week. During the last month, the stock has changed 4.56% and performed -12.57% over the last 6 months. The Volatility was noted at 1.78% in recent month and it observed Weekly Volatility of 1.62%. The Beta factor for the stock is listed at 1.38. The mean rating score for this stock is at 2.10. In current trading day Mueller Water Products, Inc. (MWA) stock confirmed the flow of -0.93% with the final price of $11.69. Its Average True Range (ATR) value figured out at 0.20. It has a Return on Investment (ROI) of 9.70% and a gross margin of 32.10%. The Company dividend yield observed at 1.37%.Technical Snapshot: The last closing stock price represents a downfall of -17.68% in price from company’s fifty two-Week high price and indicates a 11.87% above from its 52-Week low price. The recent closing stock price lost -5.25% when it compared to 200-day moving average. The stock share price surged 2.58% comparing to its 20-day moving average. The stock price is moving upward 2.27% to its 50-day moving average. A simple moving average (SMA) is an arithmetic moving average calculated by adding the closing price of the security for a number of time periods and then dividing this total by the number of time periods. A simple moving average smoothes out volatility, and makes it easier to view the price trend of a security. If the simple moving average points up, this means that the security’s price is increasing. If it is pointing down it means that the security’s price is decreasing. The longer the timeframe for the moving average, the smoother the simple moving average. A shorter-term moving average is more volatile but its reading is closer to the source data.    RELATED ARTICLESMORE FROM AUTHORTanger Factory Outlet Centers, Inc. (SKT) Stock image with current supportive move of 0.11%CME Group Inc. (CME) Stock image with current supportive move of 0.36%Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc. (MMC) Stock image with current supportive move of 0.46%LEAVE A REPLY Cancel replyPlease enter your comment!
