OIL MARKETS
Welcome to the Oil and Gas Financial Journal's Oil Markets Page containing news reported with the Oil & Gas Financial Industry perspective. 

SECTIONS: OGJ150 | OGFJ100P
COMPANIES | OIL MARKET WATCH












Carrizo Oil & Gas Inc.


(CRZO)
Carrizo Oil & Gas, Inc., an independent energy company, engages in the exploration, development, and production of oil and gas primarily in the United States. The company holds interest in crude oil and liquids plays comprising Eagle Ford Shale in south Texas; the Niobrara Formation in Colorado; and the Utica Shale in eastern Ohio and northwestern Pennsylvania.










News, Products and Stock Info






Carrizo Oil & Gas to acquire Delaware Basin properties for $648M

06/29/2017
Carrizo Oil & Gas Inc. has agreed to acquire Delaware Basin properties from ExL Petroleum Management LLC (ExL), a portfolio company of Quantum Energy Partners, for $648 million in cash.
 




Carrizo Oil & Gas makes bolt-on Eagle Ford acquisition

10/25/2016
Carrizo Oil & Gas Inc. has agreed to acquire Eagle Ford Shale properties from an affiliate of Sanchez Energy Corp. for $181 million in cash.
 




Second Eagle Ford well outperforms first for Goodrich Petroleum

12/13/2010
Houston-based Goodrich Petroleum recently announced results on its second Eagle Ford shale well, established a 2011 preliminary capital expenditure budget, and issued production guidance for 2011.
 

























